        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 8 at 11:53PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1153 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 17
miles south of Wolf Creek Park, or 20 miles north of Miami, moving
south at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northeastern
Roberts County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 100 AM CDT for
the Panhandle of Texas.</instruction>
